		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.71]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=fhrugby&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>A 36 ranger would rock at hunting mammoths in EF, since with track you would find them quicker. There are many up at once and they spawn over an area too large to find them visually, even so large that some will be out of tracking range. They spawn in an arc that runs from Megan tower east across rivers to Ice Giants and south from there all the way to south east corner, and then west to south tower. Also kill the wolly spiders to get more mammoths to spawn more often and you might as well loot any spider silks they drop for sale in baz later. The mammoths tend to spwan more often near the Wayfarers camp as it is the most traveled part of the spawn area.  <br /> <br />Killing the spiders in one location will cause the mammoths to spawn closer to that area rather than someplace further away in their spawn area. I have seen mammoths spawning once soley by south wall when someone was PL low level toons by south tower and they were pulling and killing all the wolly spiders there, causing the mammoth pops to shift closer to that area. <br /> <br />Just remember to have lots of bags that can fit giant size items since the tusks are too big to fit into regular bags. And you will make more plat if you get cha steins to raise selling price to vendors. You can even make more plat per hour than killing ice gaints if you do not have competition for mammoths which sometimes you do. Ranger tend to get them first when in competition due to tracking. <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Fri Mar 11 10:20:40 2005 by fhrugby</span></i></p>
