		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=423892"><span id="Scholar">FushaesLounge</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />61 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=FushaesLounge&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Highlevel characters (55+) usually opt out for summoned arrows or use a clicky like Tolans bracer&nbsp;&nbsp;that summons hunting barbs for general use. Long range silver tipped arrows are in demand also cause they can actually do some damage to an undead target, and those are fletched. Having wasted a lot of plat and most of my time on my first character, a ranger who grandmastered in fletching, I discovered I would have probably done better to GMed in baking.  The only real plat I ever made was selling the more exoitic bows (trivial 250+) in the bazaar. <br /> <br />And by all means... if you have a cleric you can keep in your pocket... Take him with you everywhere!  Plat has a tendency to build faster when you dont have to spend your time running away or healing up. <br /> <br />To get a ballpark figure on just how much a particular arrow is worth...  offer one to the tribute master.  The points roughly equal the amount of plat the average fletched arrow is worth. Alternately... sell just one to a merchant, and see how much he will sell it back to you for.  Average the sell price with the buy back price, and that is a fair, realistic price to ask for your arrows.</p>
