		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=osser&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I never buy arrows or make my own anymore. Ever since I got this <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=23257" title="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=23257" target="akztarg">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=23257</a> there is no need. A lot of people I know have this item from our LDoN days. <br /> <br /> Take some time to see what is selling well in the bazaar. Check prices for tradeskill items like spider (and ling) silks, pelts, various baking goods like meats and eggs. Vendor farm for research items like words and pages ect. You can find that they can pull in a lot of plat if you find the right ones. To this day I still vendor farm bone chips which I sell in the bazaar. Goblins in BB drop heads and blood that sell for 4.5 plat to vendors.Remember it all adds up.  <br /> <br />As you level it becomes much easier to make plat. You'll have chances at better drops that can sell for big bucks. Plus you'll get to the point to where you'll be able to solo mobs that drop lots of coin.  <br /> <br /></p>
