		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=306634"><span id="Scholar">LanceValiant</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />261 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.21]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=LanceValiant&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I've been selling arrows in the Baz for a while now.&nbsp;&nbsp;I've got my fletching skill up to 180 by buying the components in PoK and selling everything I make in the baz.   <br /> <br />I tend to make the cheapest arrows for each skill level to skill up on and sell them for roughly twice what it costs to make them.  (Although when I say cheapest I mean the longest range of that particular type, ie small nocks.)  I'm making class 5 bone silver tipped to get my skill to 182, which cost me about 6 gold to make and I sell for 1 plat.  So the profit ratio is falling slightly as the arrows get better but mainly because I'm trying to keep the cost lower than 1 plat for a quick sale. <br /> <br />Class 1 wood point made for almost nothing will sell for 3 gold. <br /> <br />It seems that higher quality arrows do not sell quite so quickly even if they are a better 'deal' as such.  Maybe there are more people willing to buy the very cheapest at a low cost just because there are more amateaur archers out there than uber pro ranger archers. <br /> <br />Suffice to say you can sell arrows, but if you want to make much money you will have to sell a lot of them.  Once you get to a higher skill that may become more difficult. <br /> <br />But then as I was told a while ago,  skill up on arrows, make money on bows.</p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Kronkin, Dwarf Paladin of the 40th Tour - Povar Rasp <br /> <br />Roll on Aude Sapere.</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Wokingham, England</td></tr></table>
