<p><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />'endless quiver' is a 55th ranger AA ability...<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />Actually, it's a class AA, so it's level 59, and costs 9 AA to get. <br /> <br />My ranger tried the fletching route, and used really cheap arrows (with decent range) for a long time, until he was able to get a Bloody Ancille's Pouch. I could've gotten a Tolan's bracer eventually probably, but the BAC was MUCH cheaper. Having to buy the reagents (which are very cheap and stackable) didn't bother me at all. <br /> <br />You're not going to make money off of fletching for a LONG time (if ever really). You can make some pp when you get much higher skill, but it's typically not one of the &quot;big movers&quot;, like tailoring and smithing. You never know when SOE will put that big fletchable only thing in the game though (kind of like the OoW augs). I personally wouldn't hold my breath for that one though.</p>
